    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="configuration-guide">⚙️ Configuration Guide</h2>

        <h3>Grok API Key Setup (Development)</h3>
        <p><strong>For testing without an actual Grok API key:</strong></p>
        <pre><code># Run tests with graceful degradation
cd Comserv
prove -r t/model_Grok.t t/controller_AI_grok_integration.t

# Output: All 23 tests pass even without API key (graceful degradation)</code></pre>

        <h3>Grok API Key Setup (Production)</h3>

        <h4>Option 1: Environment Variable (Development)</h4>
        <pre><code>export GROK_API_KEY="xai-your-actual-api-key-here"
perl script/comserv_server.pl</code></pre>

        <h4>Option 2: Kubernetes Secret (Production)</h4>
        <pre><code># Create K8s secret
kubectl create secret generic grok-api-key \
  --from-literal=grok_api_key=xai-your-actual-api-key-here

# Mount in pod spec (deployment.yaml)
containers:
  - name: comserv
    volumeMounts:
      - name: grok-secret
        mountPath: /run/secrets
        readOnly: true
volumes:
  - name: grok-secret
    secret:
      secretName: grok-api-key
      items:
        - key: grok_api_key
          path: grok_api_key</code></pre>

        <h3>⚠️ CRITICAL: Admin UI Configuration (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)</h3>
        <div class="alert alert-warning">
            <h3>Missing: Phase 3.1 - Grok API Key Management UI</h3>
            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Currently, Grok API keys can ONLY be configured via:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Environment variable: <code>GROK_API_KEY</code></li>
                <li>Kubernetes secret: <code>/run/secrets/grok_api_key</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Missing:</strong> No web UI for admins to enter/manage Grok API keys at runtime</p>
            <p><strong>Action Required (Task 3.1):</strong> Create admin interface for API key management</p>
            <p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Store securely in environment-specific config table or encrypted credentials table</p>
        </div>
    </div>

