        <h3>Phase 3: Configuration UI (✅ COMPLETE - 2026-01-07)</h3>
        <h4>Task 3.1: Create Admin API Key Configuration Interface ✅ COMPLETE</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>✅ File: <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Admin.pm</code> (added 209 lines)</li>
            <li>✅ Controller action: <code>/admin/ai/configure</code> (lines 2116-2319)</li>
            <li>✅ Methods implemented:
                <ul>
                    <li>ai_configure() - Display form and list existing configs</li>
                    <li>_handle_ai_config_post() - Route POST actions</li>
                    <li>_add_ai_config() - Create new AI config with validation</li>
                    <li>_edit_ai_config() - Update existing configuration</li>
                    <li>_delete_ai_config() - Remove configuration</li>
                    <li>_test_api_key() - Validate API key connection (JSON response)</li>
                    <li>_validate_api_key() - Core validation logic</li>
                    <li>_error_response() - Error handling helper</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>✅ Form template: <code>Comserv/root/admin/AiConfiguration.tt</code> (366 lines)</li>
            <li>✅ Supports multiple providers: Grok, Ollama, OpenAI</li>
            <li>✅ Storage: AiModelConfig table with encrypted api_key_encrypted column</li>
            <li>✅ Validation: Test connection before save (non-blocking, informational only)</li>
            <li>✅ Security: API keys encrypted using Crypt::CBC with Crypt::OpenSSL::AES</li>
            <li>✅ UI Features:
                <ul>
                    <li>Add new configuration form with 6 fields</li>
                    <li>Auto-populate endpoints by provider</li>
                    <li>Toggle API key visibility with eye icon</li>
                    <li>Test connection button (AJAX, non-blocking)</li>
                    <li>Existing configurations table with edit/delete actions</li>
                    <li>Bootstrap 5 responsive design</li>
                    <li>Configuration guide with links to provider consoles</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>✅ Error handling: Comprehensive try-catch with logging</li>
            <li>✅ Logging: All actions logged via Comserv::Util::Logging</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Phase 4: Advanced Features (NOT STARTED)</h3>
        <h4>Task 4.1: Web UI Provider Selection</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>⏳ Add provider dropdown to <code>root/ai/index.tt</code></li>
            <li>⏳ JavaScript: Pass provider parameter to <code>/ai/generate</code></li>
            <li>⏳ Role-based visibility (admin/developer only)</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Task 4.2: Provider Fallback Chain</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>⏳ If Grok fails → fallback to Ollama</li>
            <li>⏳ User notification: "Grok unavailable, using Ollama"</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Task 4.3: Provider Performance Metrics</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>⏳ Track response times by provider</li>
            <li>⏳ Rate limit monitoring (Grok has 429 limits)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

